neon
when two vowels are next to each other and one is stressed

consonant sound between an unstressed vowel and the following vowel, insert a 
syllable break before the last consonant

two consonants following a stressed vowel, split them with a syllable break

syllable after each stressed vowel

go back over syllables, if one ends in a vowel, and the next
begins with /N/ and then a vowel, move the /N/ to the first syllable

